    "section_title": "Word counts",
    "section_text": "Some literary awards include a `` best novella '' award and sometimes a separate `` best novelette '' award , separately from `` best short story '' or `` best novel '' . The distinction between these categories may be entirely by word count .",
    "uid": "Novella_0",
    "intro": "A novella or mezzobula is a work of narrative prose fiction, longer than a short story but shorter than a novel. Publishers and literary award societies typically describe a novella's word count as falling between 15,000 and 40,000 words, although definitions vary. The English word novella derives from the Italian novella, feminine of novello, which means new. The novella is a common literary genre in several European languages."
